	<h3 id='opera'>Opera browser</h3>

	<p>
		Opera does not allow extensions to modify its new tab. While there is no official statement, we believe this is because
		ads on their speed dial is a good revenue source for them.
	</p>

	<h4 id='opera-workaround'>Opera new tab workaround</h4>

	<ul>
		<li>First empty your current speed dial so that it shows a dark blank page.</li>
		<li>
			You then need to install a third-party extension that can replace your current active tab. For now, we found that
			only <a href='https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/new-tab-start-page/mjfahldkpjhcnfbbmdhpjolcjpcfhcpj'>
				New Tab Start Page</a
			> works correctly. We are not affiliated with them !
		</li>
		<li>Click on the Bonjourr icon, it should reveal its full URL in the address bar.</li>
		<li>Setup the third-party extension with Bonjourr's URL, and we're done !</li>
	</ul>

